    <description>NC (Notation-as-Code) â€” Write AI-powered APIs in plain English.

NC is a new programming language designed for building AI services with zero boilerplate.
Instead of complex frameworks, write readable English-like code that compiles to a fast native binary.

Features:
- Plain English syntax (no brackets, no semicolons)
- Built-in AI integration (OpenAI, Anthropic, Ollama, any API)
- HTTP server with routing, middleware, CORS
- JSON, WebSocket, database support built-in
- Single ~400KB binary, zero runtime dependencies
- 10x less code than Python/Node.js equivalents

Usage:
  nc version              Show version
  nc "show 42 + 8"        Run inline code
  nc run service.nc       Run a .nc file
  nc serve service.nc     Start HTTP server
    </description>
